      "content": "The idea that harsh penalties deter crime is a classic example of \"tough on crime\" rhetoric that ignores decades of data showing these laws do not actually reduce crime rates. Research consistently proves that the certainty of punishment matters far more than the severity, meaning we should focus on catching and prosecuting offenders rather than just making sentences longer. Relying on extreme penalties only creates a cycle of incarceration that fails to protect communities while wasting taxpayer money on ineffective policies.",
